@@ -0,0 +1,45 @@
+# Property Value Calculator
+
+The property value calculator provides a quick, non-binding estimate through a
+four-step questionnaire at `/valuation`.
+
+## User flow
+
+1. Select an apartment or house.
+2. Choose the general location type.
+3. Enter the living space in square metres.
+4. Select the property's condition.
+5. View the estimated value and an approximate range of +/- 8%.
+
+Users can move between steps or restart the questionnaire after seeing the
+result. The navigation links to the calculator through the `Free valuation`
+button.
+
+## Calculation
+
+The estimate uses a deliberately simple formula:
+
+```text
+living space
+  x location price per m²
+  x property type factor
+  x condition factor
+```
+
+Location prices and adjustment factors are defined in `app/data/valuation.ts`.
+The result is rounded to a whole euro and formatted for display. This is a demo
+calculation and not a professional property appraisal.
+
+## Architecture
+
+- `app/src/App.tsx` registers the `/valuation` route.
+- `app/components/navbar.tsx` links users to the calculator.
+- `app/src/routes/Valuation.tsx` manages the questionnaire state, validation,
+  progress, navigation, and result view.
+- `app/components/valuation-choice.tsx` renders the reusable selectable answer
+  cards.
+- `app/data/valuation.ts` owns the input types, calculation factors, formula,
+  and currency formatting.
+
+Keeping calculation logic outside the route separates domain rules from the UI
+and makes the factors easier to adjust without changing the questionnaire.
